---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const lastUpdated = 'January 11, 2026';
---

<BaseLayout title="Terms of Service">
  <main class="policy">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
      <p class="meta">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

      <section>
        <h2>Using the App</h2>
        <p>
          The Vydio app helps creators improve channel performance by adjusting video metadata
          and related assets. You must connect a YouTube account you own or are authorized to manage.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Data from YouTube APIs</h2>
        <p>
          The app uses the YouTube Data API and YouTube Analytics API to fetch video and channel metadata
          (including titles, descriptions, thumbnails, tags, and comments) and performance information for
          the authenticated channel. Access is limited to the scopes required to deliver the app&apos;s
          optimization features.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Updating Video Metadata</h2>
        <p>
          When you approve changes in the app, we update video metadata (such as titles, descriptions,
          tags, and thumbnails) on your behalf through the YouTube APIs. You remain responsible for the
          accuracy and appropriateness of any updates you accept.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>No Sharing with Third-Party AI Services</h2>
        <p>
          Data returned from the YouTube Data API and YouTube Analytics API is not sent to external AI
          services. We do not use your data to train AI models or allow third parties to use it for
          advertising or unrelated purposes.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Performance Expectations and Liability</h2>
        <p>
          The app is designed to follow industry best practices and YouTube recommendations to improve
          channel performance. However, results are not guaranteed. The app cannot be held responsible for
          decreased performance, including when user choices (for example, drastic manual changes to
          descriptions or hashtags) negatively affect results. Use the app at your own discretion.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>User Responsibilities</h2>
        <p>
          You agree to use the app in compliance with YouTube&apos;s Terms of Service and all applicable
          laws. You are responsible for all actions taken through your account and for reviewing any changes
          before they are applied.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .policy {
    padding: var(--spacing-3xl) 0 var(--spacing-2xl);
    background: var(--gradient-bg);
  }

  h1 {
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-sm);
  }

  .meta {
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-2xl);
  }

  section {
    background: var(--color-bg-elevated);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    padding: var(--spacing-xl);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-lg);
    box-shadow: 0 12px 30px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05);
  }

  section h2 {
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-sm);
  }

  section p {
    margin: 0;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .policy {
      padding: var(--spacing-2xl) 0 var(--spacing-xl);
    }

    section {
      padding: var(--spacing-lg);
    }
  }
</style>

